        <!-- SECTION 1: THE PHYSICS OF FAILURE -->
        <!-- 
            Goal: Explain why traditional ventilation fails in high-rises.
            Vis: Stacked Bar Chart comparing Forces (Fan Pressure vs Stack Effect).
        -->
        <section id="problem" class="scroll-mt-20">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-4">The Physics of Failure</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                        Traditional ventilation relies on transporting waste air through massive vertical shafts. In high-rise buildings, this fights against formidable physical forces. The <strong>Stack Effect</strong> (thermal buoyancy) creates pressure columns that fight roof fans, while the <strong>Wind Dam Effect</strong> creates backdrafts at horizontal terminations. The result? "Dead Zones" where odors stagnate.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-4">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-orange-100 flex items-center justify-center text-orange-600 font-bold text-sm mt-1">1</span>
                            <span class="ml-4 text-slate-700"><strong>Vertical Constraint:</strong> Thermal buoyancy creates up to 250 Pa of pressure differential in tall towers, neutralizing standard fan curves.</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="flex-shrink-0 h-6 w-6 rounded-full bg-orange-100 flex items-center justify-center text-orange-600 font-bold text-sm mt-1">2</span>
                            <span class="ml-4 text-slate-700"><strong>Horizontal Constraint:</strong> Wind loading on facades acts as a "dam," preventing exhaust and causing re-entrainment into balconies.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-slate-100 card-hover">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-800 mb-4 text-center">Pressure Conflict: Fan vs. Nature</h3>
                    <div class="chart-container">
                        <canvas id="stackEffectChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-xs text-center text-slate-400 mt-2">Comparison of Mechanical Fan Pressure vs. Counter-acting Natural Forces in a 50-Story Building</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 2: THE SOLUTION (KILL & CAPTURE) -->
